#command

# Move to the next file with the left and right arrow keys.
\kr         next-file
\kl         prev-file
# Inspiration: http://linuxgazette.net/174/grebler.html

# Map the l and h keys to scroll right and left.
# This means help must be accessed with H, not h.
# If you need to scroll e.g. one char to the left, type 1h.
l           right-scroll
h           left-scroll
# https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/59188/how-to-set-up-hjkl-for-less

# Make j/k/f move endlessly
j           forw-line-force
k           back-line-force
f           forw-screen-force
